          "body": "The four ask *when* and *what sign* (13:4). Jesus answers neither. Instead He gives them four imperatives (*blepete*, 13:5, 9, 23, 33), one promise of mission (13:10), one promise of endurance (13:13), and one explicit refusal to disclose timing (13:32). The shift is pastoral genius. Curiosity about timing is the perennial disciple's distraction; it diverts energy from obedience into speculation. By refusing to answer *when*, Jesus liberates His disciples for the only question that actually matters: *how do we live faithfully now?* Every generation since has been tempted to repeat the disciples' question. Every generation hears Jesus' refusal."
